com.exacttarget.etpushsdk

Class ETAnalytics

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.exacttarget.etpushsdk.ETAnalytics
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AnalyticItemEventListener, BackgroundEventListener

    public class ETAnalytics
extends Object
implements AnalyticItemEventListener, BackgroundEventListener
    Analytics engine for Journey Builder for Apps (JB4A) SDK. Add tracking code to each Activity in your application. ETAnalytics will send its data 2 seconds after the last time activityPaused() method is called on ETPush. If you're switching between activities in a foreground app, this will *not* trigger a data upload. Only when the app truly goes into the background and no call to activityResumed() has happened for over 2 seconds will ETAnalytics upload tracking data.

    Usage:

     
 public class MyActivity extends Activity {
  ...
  @Override
  protected void onResume() {
    super.onResume();
    try {
      ETPush.pushManager().activityResumed(this);
    }
    catch(ETException e) {
      Log.e(TAG, e.getMessage(), e);
    }
  }

  @Override
  protected void onPause() {
    super.onPause();
    try {
      ETPush.pushManager().activityPaused(this);
    }
    catch(ETException e) {
      Log.e(TAG, e.getMessage(), e);
    }
  }
  ...
 }
